properties.name: Inferno Start
properties.description: The Race Starts in the parking lot directly across from Story Land on Rt 16 at 7am.  Racers will head depart the parking lot and head north on Rt 16
properties.directions: Pinkham Notch Road, Intervale, NH 03845, USA

properties.name: Run Kayak Transition
properties.description: The Run/Kayak transition zone is at Thorne Pond Conservation Area,located directly across Route 302 from Bear Peak Ski Area. The gate to the pond will be open only on race day. A parking lot and a port a potty will be available.
properties.address: Crawford Notch Road, Bartlett, NH 03812, USA

properties.name: Kayak - Bike Transition
properties.description: The Kayak Leg ends on the sandy beach at the Glen Ellis Campground on river left at mile 5.5. Drag the boat out of the water,and then run to kayak/bike transition zone

properties.name: Bike - Hike Transition
properties.description: The bike / hike transition zone is in the dirt parking lot for theDeritissma Trail, which is on the left, just before the AMC Pinkham Notch Visitor Center.
properties.address: White Mountain Road, White Mountain National Forest, Jackson, NH 03846, USA

properties.name: Hike - Ski Transition
properties.description: The actual Hike-Ski Transition will be determined during the week prior to the race based on prevailing conditions.  The hiker must arrive at the Hike / Ski transition zone by 1PM or the skier may be disqualified
properties.directions: Tuckerman Ravine Trail, White Mountain National Forest, Jackson, NH 03846, USA

properties.name: Top of Ski Course
properties.description: The skier will hike from the transition zone to the start of a giant slalom course set in Tuckerman Ravine. The exact course will be determined the day prior to the race based onsnow conditions and safety requirements.

properties.name: Glen Ledge Road Interseciton
properties.description: Runners will turn left here and head up the Glen Ledge Hill.  Bikers will exit the Glen Ledge Road, Cross traffic  turn left and head north on Rt 16.

properties.name: Glen Ledge - Jericho Road Interseciton
properties.description: Runners Turn Left at the T.  Bikers must turn right onto Glen Ledge Road.

properties.name: Jericho Rd Interseciton
properties.description: Runners Turn Right on to Rt 302.  Bikers Turn RIght on to Jericho Rd

properties.name: Glen Road Crossing
properties.description: Bikers Exit the Glen Ellis Campground. Cross Rt 302 turn right and head west.

properties.name: Birch Ledge Rd
properties.description: Bikers Turn RIght onto Birch Ledge Rd

properties.name: Jackson Loop
properties.description: Racers will turn left, cross the Jackson Covered bridge, proceed through Jackson Village, Past the Wentworth Hotel and Golf Course and turn right onto Rt 16 North

properties.name: Ski
properties.description: Course will consist of control gates and piste markers as set by chief of course.  Please check www.mountwashingtonavalanchecenter.org for the latest safety buliten for skiing on Mt Washington

properties.name: Race Finish
properties.description: The exact course will be determined the day prior to the race based on snow conditions and safety requirements.

properties.name: Hike
properties.address: Tuckerman Ravine Trail, White Mountain National Forest, Jackson, NH 03846, USA

properties.name: Blanchard Loop Ski Trail
properties.description: The hiker will be tagged by the biker at the transition zone at the Deritissma Trailhead parking lot. The hiker will proceed across the foot bridge and around the perimeter of the south end of the AMC parking lot to the Blanchard Loop Ski Trail.The hiker will continue up the Blanchard Loop Trail turning right onto the Tuckerman Ravine Trail.

properties.name: Hermit Lake Shelter
properties.description: At Hermit Lake Shelter, hikers are to follow a course marked by traffic cones around the perimeter of the courtyard.  This is a public,busy spot on the course and competitors must make efforts to minimize impact on other public users of the area.
